        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 2:52PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Shelby, or near Patterson Springs, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shelby, Kings Mountain, Boiling Springs NC, Patterson Springs, Waco,
Earl, and Grover.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
